<subSubSection id="72A1650E0A120925379BFAE1C712FA98" pageId="2" pageNumber="424" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3A0436850A120925379BFAE1C712FA98" blockId="2.[151,1437,1297,1468]" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A120925379BFAE1C74AFAE3" bold="true" box="[151,274,1297,1323]" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="FDBB4D060A1209253534FAE3C4B6FAE4" authorityName="Li" authorityYear="2011" box="[568,750,1298,1324]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Phlogothamnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutaedeagus">
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A1209253534FAE3C4B6FAE4" box="[568,750,1298,1324]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">P. acutaedeagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by the crown and forewing without black markings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
